Differentiation_protocol:
The cells were
grown to confluency at 378C for 8 days in Dulbecco’s modified

Eagle’s medium (MEM)/F-12 (1:1) containing phenol red (Sigma-
Aldrich) on 24-well plates (Nunc, Roskilde, Denmark) in a

humidified atmosphere containing 5% CO2. l-Glutamine (4 mM;
Gibco, Budapest, Hungary), penicillin (200 units/ml; Gibco),
streptomycin (200 Ag/ml; Gibco), MEM nonessential amino acids
(Gibco), and 10 AM all-trans retinoic acid (RA; Sigma-Aldrich)
were dissolved in DMSO. The final concentrations of all-trans
retinoic acid and DMSO were 10 AM and 0.5%, respectively, and
10% fetal bovine serum (FBS; Gibco) was added to the medium.
On the first day, the number of nondifferentiated cells in the wells
was 2.5  105 cells/ml. After 8 days of differentiation, the cells
attached to the plate as a monolayer, and cell counting indicated
3  105 cells/cm2 (corresponding to 6.5  105 cells/ml in
suspension).

Differentiation_protocol:
After an overnight period where cells were
allowed to attach to cultureware surface,
differentiation was initiated by changing the
complete media to a reduced serum media (1%
Heat-inactivated FBS in 1:1 phenol free
DMEM/F12 supplemented with 1% PenStrep and
1% Glutamax). This reduced serum media was
supplemented with 10 μM all-trans retinoic acid
(RA) with a DMSO concentration of 0.5% for up
to 4 days with RA medium changes every 2 days.

Differentiation_protocol:
Prior
to use, SH-SY5Y cells were differentiated with trans retinoic
acid (10 μM) and recombinant human brain derived nerve
growth factor (50 ng/ml; Peprotech, Rehovot, Israel) in
serum-free neurobasal medium supplemented with N2 and
B27 supplements for 1 week to restrict the unnecessary proliferation of cells and obtain mature neuronal phenotype.
OBS:

also run parallel under identical conditions.

Differentiation_protocol:
To test the inhibitory effect of compounds on the neuronal toxicity,
SH-SY5Y human neuroblastoma cells were plated on a 96-well plate
and cultured in a humidified 5% CO2 atmosphere in DMEM:F-12 (1:1)
with phenol red, to which L-glutamine, penicillin, streptomycin, MEM

non-essential amino acids, 10% FBS, 0.5% DMSO, and 10 lM all-
trans retinoic acid (RA) as differentiating agent were added. After 8

days, the supernatant was removed with a pipette and a new medium
(with 0.2% FBS, 2% DMSO, free from phenol red, RA) containing
5 lM Ab42 or a mixture of 5 lM Ab42 and 10 lM of each compound
was added to each cell
